cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the universality problem for different types of automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the computational complexity of the problem. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper involves proving the existence or non-existence of a solution. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper deals with the complexity of the problem for different types of automata. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the representation of languages by different types of automata.
